We update the COPSE model by including a feedback of bioturbation on the burial of marine organic carbon (mocb), marine organic phosphorus (mopb) and marine pyrite sulphur (mpsb). In the baseline model, marine organic carbon burial is quadratically dependent on primary production (newP), where mocb0 is an estimate for present-day marine organic carbon burial, and newP0 is an estimate of present-day primary production. We introduce a new parameter (CBbiot), which represents enhanced mineralisation by bioturbation and is defined as:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
